More on hair physiology, but a friend told me he started growing chest hair for the first time when he spent some time in Croatia and attributed it to Zagreb having very mineral-dense tap water, saying it even left a white mineraly residue coating on objects. Very hard tap water.

He said he later got the same effect from drinking a bunch of bottles of Fever Tree tonic water (good brand) every day so Quinine might have a similar effect somehow. But I guess Georgians have very hard, mineral-heavy water (e.g. Borjomi) and they tend to be very hairy. Curious.
